<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,1796]" pageId="23" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,402,1267,1292]" pageId="23" pageNumber="366">Color in alcohol.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[420,504,1268,1292]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,337,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,337,1957]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Holotype of Ancistrus vericaucanus, MPUJ 6020 (72.1 mm SL)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219667/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="366">
Fig. 
<number box="[475,504,1268,1292]" pageId="23" pageNumber="366" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) Dorsal and lateral base color dark gray to brown mottled with light brown, and sometimes lighter brown spots concentrated top of head. Soft nose and tentacles also dark with irregular lighter spots. Some plates of dorsum dark brown edged in lighter brown. All fins with three-four alternating dark brown to black and light brown spots present on spine and branched rays. Fin membranes usually not spotted except on caudal fin. Dark spots on rays of caudal fin not aligning to form vertical bars or arcs. Ventral surface of head and abdomen tan with large irregular lighter spots and vermiculations. Oral disk whitish. Base of caudal fin with light tan area on dorsal and ventral margin of caudal peduncle, but not forming complete light vertical bar. Color in life not available.
</paragraph>
